<section class="historia">
  <div class="container historia__wrapper">
    <div class="historia__main-grid">
      <div class="historia__content">
        <p>
          The Comprehensive Artistic Pedagogical Center (C.A.P.I.) emerged in
          2021 as a landmark space in Samaipata, founded by
          <strong>Liliana Navía</strong> and <strong>Mónica Navía</strong>. Since
          its inception, the project was conceived as an autonomous, non-profit
          entity dedicated to enriching the community's cultural life and
          providing accessible services that foster a sense of belonging among
          local families.
        </p>
        <p>
          Through independent and passionate management, our founders,
          <strong>Liliana</strong> and <strong>Mónica</strong>, have established
          a breeding ground for talent where art and pedagogy merge. This
          constant effort seeks not only technical training but also the
          strengthening of the social fabric, preparing the ground to address
          the current challenges faced by children and youth.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="historia__image">
        <img src="/assets/img/quienes_somos.webp" alt="CAPI Founders" />
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="historia__filosofia">
      <p>
        C.A.P.I. was born as a necessary response to the challenges facing
        today's youth. In a world marked by digital isolation and school
        disinterest, we have built a dynamic space that combats the feeling of
        lack of understanding. We work to bridge the generational gap,
        understanding that art is the perfect bridge for communication between
        parents, teachers, and young people.
      </p>

      <p>
        Our work transcends academic training. We operate under a vision of
        emotional well-being and autonomy, providing accessible services so that
        every family in Samaipata finds an ally in us. Here, every student is a
        potential talent who deserves a safe environment to project their future
        with confidence.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

